---
// One idea: you mend at the speed the mending happens — a real recovery is a
// jagged rising line, not the straight one you'd have willed.
---
<svg width="560" height="200" viewBox="0 0 560 200" role="img" aria-labelledby="mend-t">
  <title id="mend-t">Two lines from low to recovered. A faint straight diagonal marked "the pace I willed" is crossed out. The real recovery is a jagged line that dips and returns, climbing overall to the same height the slow way.</title>
  <path class="ink hair" d="M40 160 L 520 60" stroke-dasharray="3 6" opacity="0.4" />
  <text class="hand-label" x="60" y="150" font-size="13" opacity="0.55">the pace I willed</text>
  <path class="ink hair" d="M150 120 L 176 96 M176 120 L 150 96" stroke="var(--poppy)" opacity="0.5" />
  <path class="ink spine" d="M40 168 C 90 150, 110 168, 150 150 C 190 132, 210 156, 250 132 C 300 104, 320 128, 360 104 C 410 78, 440 96, 520 64" stroke="var(--poppy)" />
  <circle class="port-fill" cx="40" cy="168" r="3.4" /><circle class="port-fill" cx="520" cy="64" r="3.4" />
  <text class="hand-label hand-label--accent" x="330" y="150" font-size="14">mend at the mending&rsquo;s own pace</text>
</svg>
